parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbag deployment can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None of the passenger side airbags deployed in a crash
including the front passenger
front side
or rear passenger side airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to replace the recalled Takata airbags can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Receiving multiple recall notices without being able to schedule a repair due to lack of parts
dealerships not having parts or not being aware of the recall
being told to wait for an unknown amount of time for parts to become available
and lack of communication from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure Causing Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle surges or lurches forward
the "PRNDS" light on the dashboard flashes
and the vehicle goes into neutral or limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight internal coil can cause the headlights to stop functioning, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights flicker and then go out
console message "Right/Left Headlight Dipped" appears
intermittent headlight malfunction
headlight fails to come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty design in the tail-lights can cause the brake lights to fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Melted brake light/tail-light housing
brake lights fail
bulbs are good and functional
but circuit is affected.
